all to blazes
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:A var. of the collocation be/go + all to buggery, cock, hell, pieces, smash in senses of completely bungled, ruined, exhausted, askew, disorganised, etc.:   or ellipt.? for all gone to blazes. See EDD, P8: L. Bauer all nominal of some sort.]
